{"parentUuid":"09344907-90f5-4c28-bada-918543d67a90","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/tmp/sea-smoke-1179794087","sessionId":"30755cf5-387a-4d6e-912b-b115e2fdb4ba","version":"2.1.72","gitBranch":"main","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"You are running a smoke test for agentsea sandbox isolation. Follow these steps exactly:\n\n1. Use the Team tool to spawn exactly 1 teammate with these instructions:\n\nTEAMMATE INSTRUCTIONS:\n---\nYou are a smoke test agent. Run ALL of these checks using the Bash tool and report results:\n\nCHECK 1 - NAMESPACE: Run: cat /proc/self/cgroup 2>/dev/null; ls /proc/self/ns/user -la\nReport PASS if you see namespace indicators (any output from ns/user shows user namespace is active).\n\nCHECK 2 - TMP ISOLATION: Run: touch /tmp/sea-smoke-canary-$$ && ls /tmp/sea-smoke-canary-$$ && rm /tmp/sea-smoke-canary-$$; echo \"TMPFS_ENTRIES=$(ls /tmp/ | wc -l)\"\nReport PASS if you can write to /tmp (it is writable tmpfs) AND the number of entries is small (less than 10, meaning it is isolated from the host's real /tmp which would have many more files).\n\nCHECK 3 - HOME ISOLATION: Run: ls $HOME\nReport what you see. PASS if you see a restricted set of files (not the user's full home directory like dotfiles, project, snap, etc).\n\nCHECK 4 - WORKTREE: Run: git branch --show-current && pwd\nReport the branch and working directory. PASS if you are on a branch like smoke-agent/work.\n\nCHECK 5 - READ-ONLY ROOT: Run: touch /usr/local/sea-smoke-test 2>&1 || echo READONLY\nReport PASS if READONLY or \"Read-only file system\".\n\nAfter running all checks, write your results to smoke-results.txt in the current directory, one check per line:\nCHECK 1: PASS/FAIL - details\nCHECK 2: PASS/FAIL - details\nCHECK 3: PASS/FAIL - details\nCHECK 4: PASS/FAIL - details\nCHECK 5: PASS/FAIL - details\n---\n\n2. After spawning the teammate, poll for results every 15 seconds. The teammate writes smoke-results.txt in its worktree at .agentsea/agents/smoke-agent/repo/smoke-results.txt relative to the project root. Run:\ncat .agentsea/agents/smoke-agent/repo/smoke-results.txt 2>/dev/null || echo \"NOT READY YET\"\nKeep polling until the file exists and contains CHECK results. Do NOT stop until you have the results.\n\n3. Once you have the results, write them to smoke-results.txt in the PROJECT ROOT (not the agent repo). Use the Bash tool:\ncat .agentsea/agents/smoke-agent/repo/smoke-results.txt > smoke-results.txt\nThis file signals completion to the test harness.\n\n4. If any check fails, explain what went wrong."},"uuid":"fadc8ad4-1de0-45ae-ba7b-cbe5966a8b83","timestamp":"2026-03-11T01:49:00.771Z","permissionMode":"bypassPermissions"}
